# 🛡️ Azure Storage Data Exfiltration Detection with Microsoft Sentinel

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates a cloud security monitoring lab built using **Microsoft Azure**, **Azure Storage**, **Log Analytics Workspace**, **Microsoft Sentinel**, and **KQL**.

The main goal of this project is to detect suspicious Azure Blob Storage download activity that may indicate **possible data exfiltration**. In this lab, fake sensitive files were uploaded to a private Azure Blob container, diagnostic logs were enabled, and Microsoft Sentinel was used to detect repeated blob download operations from the same source.

This project follows a basic SOC workflow:

```text
Log Collection → KQL Detection → Sentinel Analytics Rule → Alert → Incident → Investigation
🎯 Objective

The objective of this lab is to understand how cloud storage access can be monitored and investigated using Microsoft Sentinel.

This project focuses on detecting:

Multiple blob downloads from the same IP address
Suspicious access to cloud storage
Possible exposed SAS token usage
Possible compromised credential activity
Possible cloud data exfiltration behavior

