⚙️ Project Workflow
Created an Azure Storage Account.
Created a private Blob container.
Uploaded fake sensitive files for testing.
Enabled diagnostic settings for Blob Storage.
Sent StorageRead, StorageWrite, and StorageDelete logs to Log Analytics Workspace.
Queried storage activity using KQL.
Created a Microsoft Sentinel scheduled analytics rule.
Generated a Sentinel alert and incident.
Investigated the incident using a SOC-style workflow.
Mapped the detection to MITRE ATT&CK techniques.

🔍 Detection Logic

The detection identifies repeated GetBlob operations from the same IP address within a short time window.

In a real-world environment, this type of activity may indicate:

Suspicious file download activity
Exposed SAS token usage
Compromised credentials
Insider threat activity
Possible data exfiltration from cloud storage

🧪 KQL Detection Query

The KQL query used in this project is available in the repository:

kql/storage-exfiltration-detection.kql

Main detection logic:

let downloadThreshold = 5;
StorageBlobLogs
| where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
| where OperationName == "GetBlob"
| where tostring(StatusCode) startswith "2"
| summarize
    DownloadCount = count(),
    TotalBytesDownloaded = sum(tolong(ResponseBodySize)),
    FirstSeen = min(TimeGenerated),
    LastSeen = max(TimeGenerated),
    TimeGenerated = max(TimeGenerated),
    FilesAccessed = make_set(Uri, 20)
    by CallerIpAddress, AuthenticationType, AccountName
| where DownloadCount >= downloadThreshold
| project TimeGenerated, AccountName, CallerIpAddress, AuthenticationType, DownloadCount, TotalBytesDownloaded, FirstSeen, LastSeen, FilesAccessed
| order by DownloadCount desc

🚨 Sentinel Alert & Incident

A Microsoft Sentinel analytics rule was created to automatically detect suspicious blob download activity.

When the rule matched the detection condition, Microsoft Sentinel generated an incident named:

Possible Azure Storage Data Exfiltration

The incident was investigated by reviewing:

Source IP address
Storage account name
Authentication type
Download count
Accessed files
Alert severity
Incident timeline
🧠 MITRE ATT&CK Mapping
Tactic	Technique	Technique ID	Reason
Collection	Data from Cloud Storage	T1530	Detects access and download activity from Azure cloud storage
Exfiltration	Exfiltration Over Web Service	T1567	Suspicious downloads may indicate data leaving the cloud environment

